---
<BaseLayout
  title="Owner Builder Course WA - Form 75 Ready, Online $179"
  description="WA-specific owner builder course, online and self-paced. Your certificate supports your Form 75 owner-builder approval. $179, same-day certificate, independently reviewed for currency."
  canonical={canonical}
  schema={schema}
  nav={nav}
  navCta={cta}
  sticky={{ label: 'WA Owner Builder', sub: 'supports your Form 75', price: '$179', cta: { href: '#enrol', label: 'Get your certificate' } }}
>
  <Hero
    eyebrow="WA Owner Builder · supports your Form 75 approval"
    h1Html={'Owner Builder Course WA<span class="dot">.</span>'}
    updated="Course v2.0, updated June 2026 · Reviewed for currency by Warwick Smith, 4 Jun 2026"
    subhead="The WA-specific online course that gives you the knowledge the Building Services Board requires, and supports your Form 75 owner-builder approval. Written for Western Australia, reviewed for currency, and finished in an afternoon."
    ticks={['WA-specific content, current for 2026', 'Your certificate supports your Form 75 approval', '100% online and self-paced, same-day certificate', 'Independently reviewed for currency (4 Jun 2026)']}
    cta={cta}
    proof={[{ n: 'WA', text: 'specific, reviewed for currency' }, { n: '31,000+', text: 'students trained' }, { n: '2007', text: 'training since' }]}
    howItWorks="Enrol → Complete online → Get your certificate → Lodge Form 75"
    artefactDesc="Certificate of Completion shown in product context, on a tablet or desk, Western Australian residential setting."
    artefactSpec="5:4 · warm tone · ~640×512"
  />

  <Section bg="bg-alt" eyebrow="At a glance" h2="The facts before you enrol">
    <AnswerCapsule>WA runs a knowledge-requirement model, so this WA-specific course plus a White Card is the evidence the Building Services Board accepts for your Form 75 approval. It is <b>$179</b>, 100% online, the quiz needs <b>80%</b> to pass, and your certificate is issued the <b>same day</b>.</AnswerCapsule>
    <FactGrid items={glance} />
  </Section>

  <section class="sec" id="course"><div class="wrap">
    <ZSplit imgDesc="Owner builder reviewing plans on a Western Australian residential site." imgSpec="4:5 · warm tone · ~520×650">
      <span class="marker"><span class="current">01</span> / {TOTAL}</span>
      <span class="eyebrow">The course</span>
      <h2 class="h2">Is this course accepted for WA owner-builder approval?</h2>
      <AnswerCapsule><b>Yes.</b> Western Australia does not prescribe a specific owner-builder course. The Building Services Board accepts a WA-specific course completed within the last two years, together with a White Card, as evidence that you understand an owner-builder’s duties. ABE’s certificate is that evidence, and you attach it to your Form 75.</AnswerCapsule>
      <div class="measure">
        <p>WA runs what is called a knowledge-requirement model. Rather than approving particular courses or providers, the Building Services Board sets out the knowledge an owner-builder must have and lists the ways you can show it. The most common pathway, and the one this course is built for, is a course with WA-specific content completed within the last two years, paired with a White Card (unit CPCWHS1001).</p>
        <p>So the accurate way to describe this course is that it <strong>supports</strong> your Form 75 owner-builder approval. It is not a licence, it is not the approval itself, and no course in WA is government approved. What matters to the Board is that the content is WA-specific and current, and that you hold a dated certificate you can lodge straight away.</p>
        <a class="btn-link" href="#need">See who needs approval <span class="arr" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
      </div>
      <VerifiedSources date="7 Jul 2026" sources={[{ label: 'WA — Owner-builder approval', href: 'https://www.wa.gov.au/organisation/service-delivery/owner-builder-approval' }, { label: 'BSB — Sufficient knowledge policy', href: 'https://www.wa.gov.au/system/files/2024-10/bsb_policy_-_sufficient_knowledge_of_the_duties_and_responsibilities_of_an_owner-builder.pdf' }]} />
    </ZSplit>
    <SectionWayfinder label="Licence, permit or approval?" href="#licence" />
  </div></section>

  <Section bg="bg-alt" id="licence" marker="02" total={TOTAL} eyebrow="The right word" h2="Is it a licence, a permit, or an approval?">
    <AnswerCapsule>In Western Australia it is an <b>owner-builder approval</b>, granted by the Building Services Board through Building and Energy (part of LGIRS). It is not a licence and not a permit, and there is no accredited or WA-approved version of the course. You apply on Form 75, then apply separately to your local council for the building permit.</AnswerCapsule>
    <CanCant
      canTitle="What it is"
      can={['An owner-builder approval, applied for on Form 75.', 'Granted by the Building Services Board via Building and Energy (LGIRS).', 'Evidenced by a WA-specific course completed within two years, plus a White Card.']}
      cantTitle="What it is not"
      cant={['Not a licence. That is what a registered building contractor holds.', 'Not the building permit. That is a separate application to your local council.', 'Not an accredited or WA-approved course. WA prescribes no course.']}
    />
    <Note><b>Why it matters:</b> people search for a licence or a permit, so it is worth being clear, because the wrong word points you at the wrong process. If a course still refers to the Building Commission or the Department of Mines, its WA content is out of date. Getting the current names right is the difference between a clean application and a false start.</Note>
    <VerifiedSources date="7 Jul 2026" sources={[{ label: 'WA — Owner-builder approval', href: 'https://www.wa.gov.au/organisation/service-delivery/owner-builder-approval' }, { label: 'Building Services (Registration) Act 2011', href: 'https://www.legislation.wa.gov.au/legislation/statutes.nsf/law_a146913.html' }]} />
    <SectionWayfinder label="Do you need approval?" href="#need" />
  </Section>

  <Section id="need" marker="03" total={TOTAL} eyebrow="The threshold" h2="Do you need owner-builder approval, and this course?">
    <AnswerCapsule><b>You need approval if the building work is valued over $20,000</b> and you want to take on the builder’s role yourself rather than engage a registered building contractor. To get that approval you must show the required knowledge, which is where this course and a White Card come in. Then you apply to your local council for the building permit.</AnswerCapsule>
    <div class="measure">
      <p>Under the Building Act 2011, building work valued at more than <strong>$20,000</strong> must be carried out by a registered building contractor, unless you hold owner-builder approval for that work. Approval covers a detached house (Class 1a(i)), a Class 10 non-habitable structure such as a shed, garage, carport or patio, or a small commercial building of one or two storeys under 500 square metres. A Class 10a structure valued up to $50,000 does not require approval. You cannot split a project into smaller contracts to keep each piece under the threshold.</p>
      <p><b>Who can apply:</b> you must own, or be buying, the land; approval is granted to an individual, not a company or trust; you must intend to live in, occupy or use the building; and you can hold only one approval every six years.</p>
    </div>
    <CanCant
      canTitle="What approval lets you do"
      can={['Take on the role of the builder for your own project.', 'Engage and coordinate the trades you need.', 'Be the party responsible to the regulator for the work.']}
      cantTitle="What it does not do"
      cant={['Let you do licensed electrical or plumbing work yourself.', 'Let you build to sell as a business.', 'Remove your responsibility for safety and quality on site.']}
    />
    <VerifiedSources date="7 Jul 2026" sources={[{ label: 'WA — Owner-builder approval', href: 'https://www.wa.gov.au/organisation/service-delivery/owner-builder-approval' }, { label: 'Building Act 2011', href: 'https://www.legislation.wa.gov.au/legislation/statutes.nsf/law_a146968.html' }]} />
    <SectionWayfinder label="Your responsibilities" href="#responsibilities" />
  </Section>

  <Section bg="bg-alt" id="responsibilities" marker="04" total={TOTAL} eyebrow="The role" h2="Your responsibilities as a WA owner-builder">
    <AnswerCapsule>As an owner-builder you become the person responsible for the build. That means holding the building permit and working to it, engaging licensed trades for electrical and plumbing work, meeting your work health and safety duties, supervising quality, carrying the right insurance, and fixing defects. These responsibilities are yours by law and cannot be handed off.</AnswerCapsule>
    <div class="measure">
      <p>Taking owner-builder approval means stepping into the builder’s shoes. You hold and comply with the building permit and its inspection stages. You engage appropriately licensed trades, and in WA electrical and plumbing work must be done by licensed practitioners. You carry the duties of a person conducting a business or undertaking under the Work Health and Safety Act 2020, keeping the site safe for anyone who works on or visits it. You supervise quality, keep records, arrange inspections and certifications, maintain insurance, and rectify defects.</p>
    </div>
    <Note maroon><b>Be accurate on your form:</b> provide false or misleading information in your application and you face penalties of up to $25,000 under the Building Services (Registration) Act 2011. The course walks through each duty so you take the role on with your eyes open.</Note>
    <VerifiedSources date="7 Jul 2026" sources={[{ label: 'WA — Owner-builder approval', href: 'https://www.wa.gov.au/organisation/service-delivery/owner-builder-approval' }, { label: 'Work Health and Safety Act 2020', href: 'https://www.legislation.wa.gov.au/legislation/statutes.nsf/law_a147087.html' }]} />
    <SectionWayfinder label="What it covers" href="#learn" />
  </Section>

  <Section id="learn" marker="05" total={TOTAL} eyebrow="What you'll learn" h2="Introduction plus 12 modules, written for WA">
    <AnswerCapsule>An <b>Introduction and twelve modules</b>, written for Western Australia and updated in June 2026. It runs from deciding whether owner-building suits you, through WA legislation, the National Construction Code, bushfire and site-hazard requirements, contracts and insurance, to running the build and completing it.</AnswerCapsule>
    <TopicGrid items={moduleGroupsWa} />
    <Note><b>By the end</b> {moduleOutcomeWa.replace(/^By the end you will be able to /, 'you will be able to ')}</Note>
    <VerifiedSources date="Course v2.0, 27 Jun 2026" facts="WA-specific, thresholds fact-checked Feb 2026, kept within the 2-year acceptance window." sources={[{ label: 'ABE Education — WA Owner-Builder Course modules and learning outcomes (v2.0)', href: '' }]} />
    <SectionWayfinder label="How it works" href="#how" />
  </Section>

  <section class="sec bg-alt" id="how"><div class="wrap">
    <ZSplit rev imgDesc="The online course interface on a laptop, clean and self-paced." imgSpec="4:5 · warm tone · ~520×650">
      <span class="marker"><span class="current">06</span> / {TOTAL}</span>
      <span class="eyebrow">How it works</span>
      <h2 class="h2">Three steps to your certificate</h2>
      <AnswerCapsule>Enrol, work through the <b>Introduction and 12 modules</b> and the online quiz at your own pace, and get your certificate the <b>same day</b> you pass. There is no free preview; what you get instead is a WA-specific course you can finish today and a certificate ready for Form 75.</AnswerCapsule>
      <Stepper steps={howItWorksSteps} maxWidth="480px" />
      <VerifiedSources date="7 Jul 2026" sources={[{ label: 'WA — Owner-builder approval', href: 'https://www.wa.gov.au/organisation/service-delivery/owner-builder-approval' }]} />
    </ZSplit>
    <SectionWayfinder label="What it costs" href="#cost" />
  </div></section>

  <section class="sec bg-dark trust"><div class="wrap">
    <span class="eyebrow on-dark">The numbers</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Written for WA, reviewed for currency</h2>
    <AnswerCapsule onDark>A WA-specific course, <b>Introduction plus 12 modules</b>, independently reviewed for currency on 4 June 2026, from a provider that has trained more than <b>31,000</b> students since 2007.</AnswerCapsule>
    <div class="trust-stats">
      <div class="tstat"><span class="n">WA</span><span class="l">Specific, current content</span></div>
      <div class="tstat"><span class="n num">31,000+</span><span class="l">Students trained</span></div>
      <div class="tstat"><span class="n num">19</span><span class="l">Years operating</span></div>
      <div class="tstat"><span class="n num">12</span><span class="l">Modules, plus Introduction</span></div>
    </div>
    <p class="attest">A WA-specific Certificate of Completion that supports your Form 75 owner-builder approval. This is not an RTO course and not nationally recognised training; WA prescribes no owner-builder course. ABN 64 125 455 272 · <a href="https://www.wa.gov.au/organisation/service-delivery/owner-builder-approval" rel="noopener">wa.gov.au</a></p>
  </div></section>

  <Section bg="bg-warm" id="cost" marker="07" total={TOTAL} eyebrow="What it costs" h2="Three costs, three payees, nothing hidden">
    <AnswerCapsule>The course is <b>$179</b> to ABE. The government owner-builder approval fee is a separate <b>$212</b> for residential (or $467 for industrial-commercial), paid to Building and Energy. Your local council then charges value-based building-permit fees. Only one of the three is the course.</AnswerCapsule>
    <PriceCard rows={priceRows} foot="The $179 course fee can be split into four with Afterpay. The government approval fee is set by Building and Energy and reviewed each 1 July, so confirm the current amount before you lodge. Your local council charges separate, value-based building-permit fees." />
    <h3 class="h3" style="margin-top:var(--s-2xl);margin-bottom:var(--s-2xs)">Course and White Card bundle</h3>
    <p style="max-width:62ch">The Building Services Board’s knowledge pathway asks for a WA-specific course and a White Card. If you need both, do them together for <strong>$278</strong>: the $179 owner builder course plus the $99 White Card (unit CPCWHS1001). That is the complete knowledge evidence for your Form 75 in one go.</p>
    <SectionWayfinder label="What else you need" href="#obligations" />
  </Section>

  <Section id="obligations" marker="08" total={TOTAL} eyebrow="Wider obligations" h2="What else your WA project needs">
    <AnswerCapsule>Beyond the course and approval, a few obligations apply: home indemnity insurance if you sell within seven years, workers’ compensation if you employ anyone, the timing rules on your approval, licensed trades, and the separate council building permit.</AnswerCapsule>
    <TopicGrid items={obligationCardsWa} />
    <div class="zsplit" style="margin-top:var(--s-2xl);align-items:center">
      <div class="z-body">
        <span class="eyebrow">Insurance</span>
        <h3 class="h3" style="font-size:26px;margin-bottom:var(--s-sm)">Cover for your build, through our partner</h3>
        <p style="max-width:52ch">As an owner-builder you carry the risk on your own site, so arrange the right cover before work starts. Most owner-builders need public liability and contract works cover, and if you sell within seven years of the building permit you must have home indemnity insurance in place.</p>
        <p style="max-width:52ch">ABE Education is not a licensed insurance provider. We work with our insurance partner InsuranceTek Pty Ltd, whose principal broker Mark Adams has helped ABE students for close to 20 years. We can introduce you for a quote and advice tailored to your project.</p>
        <a class="btn-secondary" href="#enrol">Get an owner builder insurance quote</a>
      </div>
      <div class="z-img"><Placeholder ratio="r54" desc="Western Australian owner-builder site with materials, suggesting the risk that cover protects." spec="5:4 · warm tone · ~640×512" /></div>
    </div>
    <Note><b>Please note:</b> this is general information, not a complete list of the cover you may need. Insurance is arranged by InsuranceTek Pty Ltd, not ABE Education.</Note>
    <VerifiedSources date="7 Jul 2026" sources={[{ label: 'WA — Owner-builder approval', href: 'https://www.wa.gov.au/organisation/service-delivery/owner-builder-approval' }, { label: 'Home Building Contracts Act 1991', href: 'https://www.legislation.wa.gov.au/legislation/statutes.nsf/law_a306.html' }]} />
    <SectionWayfinder label="Become an owner builder" href="#become" />
  </Section>

  <Section bg="bg-alt" id="become" marker="09" total={TOTAL} eyebrow="The full path" h2="How to become an owner builder in Western Australia">
    <AnswerCapsule>Five steps: check whether your project needs approval, complete a WA-specific course and a White Card, lodge Form 75 and pay the fee, apply to your council for the building permit, then build to your approval. Approval usually takes around six weeks to process.</AnswerCapsule>
    <Stepper steps={becomeSteps} maxWidth="640px" />
    <Note maroon><b>Mind the six-month clock.</b> Your owner-builder approval lapses if you do not apply for a building permit within six months, so line the steps up before you lodge.</Note>
    <VerifiedSources date="7 Jul 2026" sources={[{ label: 'WA — Owner-builder approval', href: 'https://www.wa.gov.au/organisation/service-delivery/owner-builder-approval' }, { label: 'Form 75 (PDF)', href: 'https://www.wa.gov.au/media/50162/download' }]} />
    <SectionWayfinder label="Who develops and reviews it" href="#content-review" />
  </Section>

  <Section bg="bg-warm" id="content-review" marker="10" total={TOTAL} eyebrow="Developed and reviewed by" h2="Who develops and reviews this course">
    <AnswerCapsule>This course is <b>developed by Dominic Ogburn</b>, a licensed builder with more than forty years in Australian construction, and <b>independently reviewed by Warwick Smith</b> for compliance and currency. Warwick’s review, dated 4 June 2026, checks that the WA legislation and requirements on this page are current.</AnswerCapsule>
    <Credentials people={experts} />
    <SectionWayfinder label="FAQ" href="#faq" />
  </Section>

  <Section id="faq" marker="11" total={TOTAL} eyebrow="FAQ" h2="Common questions">
    <Faq items={faqsWa} />
    <VerifiedSources date="7 Jul 2026" sources={[{ label: 'WA — Owner-builder approval', href: 'https://www.wa.gov.au/organisation/service-delivery/owner-builder-approval' }, { label: 'Form 75 (PDF)', href: 'https://www.wa.gov.au/media/50162/download' }]} />
    <SectionWayfinder label="Get your certificate" href="#enrol" ready />
  </Section>

  <CtaBand
